  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Florist Intern",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Assist florists in preparing and arranging fresh flower bouquets and floral designs</p></li><li><p>Learn proper flower conditioning, trimming, and care techniques</p></li><li><p>Support wrapping, packaging, and presentation of floral products</p></li><li><p>Assist with daily flower preparation, inventory checking, and stock organisation</p></li><li><p>Help maintain cleanliness and organisation of the work area and cold room</p></li><li><p>Support order preparation for retail, online, and delivery orders</p></li><li><p>Carry out other ad-hoc tasks related to floristry and shop operations</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Training & Learning Scope</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Introduction to fresh flowers, foliage, and basic botanical knowledge</p></li><li><p>Hands-on training in bouquet making and wrapping techniques</p></li><li><p>Understanding flower care, storage, and handling to maintain freshness</p></li><li><p>Exposure to fast-paced operations during peak periods (festive seasons)</p></li><li><p>Learning teamwork, time management, and workplace discipline</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Interest in floristry, flowers, or plants</p></li><li><p>Willingness to learn and take instructions</p></li><li><p>Able to work in a team environment</p></li><li><p>Comfortable with standing for long hours and manual work</p></li><li><p>Responsible, punctual, and positive attitude</p></li><li><p>No prior experience required (training provided)</p></li></ul><h3><strong>What We Offer</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Practical, hands-on floristry training</p></li><li><p>Supportive learning environment</p></li><li><p>Exposure to real-world florist operations</p></li><li><p>Opportunity to progress to part-time or full-time florist roles based on performance</p></li></ul>",
